    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-11-09T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-11-09T10:00:00-05:00" n="502"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d502">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">701.5214/10: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Drew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-11-09T09:00:00-06:00"
                            >November 9, 1936—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>76. Guatemalan Government yesterday sent telegram of recognition to Spanish rebel
                        government<note n="91" xml:id="d502fn91">See telegram No. X–317, November
                        17, noon, from the Embassy in Spain, <ref target="#pg_760">p.
                        760</ref>.</note> and has received as Chargé d’Affaires Francisco Lopez
                    Escobar, former Chargé d’Affaires of the Spanish Republic.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Drew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
